## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This STP defines the test strategy, scope, approach, and resources for verifying KB System Upgrade v0.6.0 across all 3 MCP server implementations (Node.js, Kotlin, Python). It covers 4 features (F1-F4), 15 user stories, 22 business rules, and 14 use cases.

### 1.2 Scope

**In Scope:** - Feature F1: Core/Archival Memory (Pinned Entries + Auto-Recall) - Feature F2: Structured Conversation History - Feature F3: Structured Map (Entity Extraction + Metadata Enrichment) - Feature F4: KB Anti-Pattern Protection (Quality Gate, Agent Scope, Token Budget, Auto-Expiry) - Cross-feature integration (F1+F3, F1+F4, F2+F3, F3+F4) - All 3 server implementations: Node.js, Kotlin, Python - Schema migrations (V3.1–V3.8) - Regression testing of 14 existing MCP tools - Performance targets (pin <50ms, conversation <100ms, extraction <200ms)

**Out of Scope:** - UI testing (system is MCP server, no UI) - Load/stress testing beyond stated performance targets - Security penetration testing - LLM-assisted extraction (deferred to future version) - Multi-tenant scenarios

