## 6. Risk Assessment

### 6.1 Test Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| Cross-server behavior inconsistency | High | Medium | E2E-API tests run identical scenarios on all 3 servers |
| SQLite version differences across servers | Medium | Low | Pin SQLite version in dependencies |
| ONNX model loading slow in CI | Low | Medium | Cache model in CI, skip embedding tests if unavailable |
| Flaky tests due to timing (expiry) | Medium | Medium | Use deterministic time mocking |
| Token counting approximation edge cases | Low | Low | PBT covers random inputs |
| Quality gate false positives | Medium | Medium | Dedicated test cases for legitimate short entries |

### 6.2 Defect Severity Classification

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Severity | Definition | Example |
| Critical | Feature completely broken, data loss | Migration corrupts existing data |
| High | Feature partially broken, workaround exists | Pin budget not enforced |
| Medium | Feature works but with issues | Incorrect entity classification |
| Low | Cosmetic or minor behavior difference | Warning message typo |

